content.description: Starts to the right of She Lives and goes straight up. Right hand in a large pocket and left hand down a bit lower.Â If anyone knows any more details about this problem, such as a name, comment and I'll change.

Slightly obscure but worthwhile. Start far right with a large sidepull hole for the right hand and a small pocket for the left. Crank left through pockets to a shouldery move and the crux reach for the namesake two-finger hole, fall into a big undercling and fire straight out to the jug at the lip.
content.protection: A couple of pads are nice, place them wisely to protect the crux. Spotter to prevent you from rolling down the hill.
content.location: Far right on the She Lives Roof. Walk off.

content.description: Left of the finish to She Lives find some large pockets in the roof and then find your self to the lip.  Enjoy the ride.
content.protection: A nice runway of, and then a big fluffy pile of pads to belly flop into is nice to have.

content.description: A big roof with a few problems. The classic here is She Lives (V6), named for the small, humid pocket at the crux. The roof is nearly impossible to see from the trail and sees relatively little traffic.
